#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:3
#: 3d4ced6642014938835eab3ee543bdbe
msgid "How to use devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:6
#: d28ec80022ea4ce0a099ffc06ab83435
msgid ""
"This is an overview of device handling in Qubes OS. For specific devices "
"(:doc:`block </user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-block-storage-devices>`, "
":doc:`USB </user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-usb-devices>` and :doc:`PCI "
"</user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-pci-devices>` devices), please visit their "
"respective pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:8
#: 772a8286152246cabea848ea3747d64b
msgid ""
"**Important security warning:** Device handling comes with many security "
"implications. Please make sure you carefully read and understand the "
":doc:`security considerations </user/security-in-qubes/device-handling-"
"security>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:11
#: cb63eca933a346dea73e3cec90b5dee9
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr "Présentation"

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:14
#: 06529cb83eab49c49e06dd2e3779c777
msgid ""
"The interface to deal with devices of all sorts was unified in Qubes 4.0 "
"with the ``qvm-device`` command and the Qubes Devices Widget. In Qubes 3.X, "
"the Qubes VM Manager dealt with attachment as well. This functionality was "
"moved to the Qubes Device Widget, the tool tray icon with a yellow square "
"located in the top right of your screen by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:16
#: b776fcd893e74714a18b87a99fbf3fb0
msgid "There are currently four categories of devices Qubes understands:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:18
#: 11b3749b12164a11a2c07a3bb34695ca
msgid "Microphones"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:20
#: 247fbc024c9f45d989a47fd27d6baacc
msgid "Block devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:22
#: f047c62cb1e74a73a5c0b787a72ec678
msgid "USB devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:24
#: 837637ce30864c7e844e1699ca6ad9a1
msgid "PCI devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:28
#: 8f47aabcdf404f6ca4ab8a643863b1ca
msgid ""
"Microphones, block devices and USB devices can be attached with the GUI-"
"tool. PCI devices can be attached using the Qube Settings, but require a VM "
"reboot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:31
#: 42588d81a5424f1a89feafdeba958df3
msgid "General Qubes Device Widget Behavior And Handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:34
#: 4542b0f3f52343b78e5443de478caf24
msgid ""
"When clicking on the tray icon (which looks similar to this): |SD card and "
"thumbdrive| several device-classes separated by lines are displayed as "
"tooltip. Block devices are displayed on top, microphones one below and USB-"
"devices at the bottom."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:167
#: 4e780a326177416aa3222de4441f775b
msgid "SD card and thumbdrive"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:36
#: 426c76e30643483dbde941a1d98e25ba
msgid ""
"On most laptops, integrated hardware such as cameras and fingerprint-readers"
" are implemented as USB-devices and can be found here."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:39
#: 71079a9ed62b40acbfe0c4f2b7af7576
msgid "Attaching Using The Widget"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:42
#: 0019a74aeb4a41a3a480ac313fe506b6
msgid ""
"Click the tray icon. Hover on a device you want to attach to a VM. A list of"
" running VMs (except dom0) appears. Click on one and your device will be "
"attached!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:45
#: 6fe3eb0faa534cd09c68ae75a682a00f
msgid "Detaching Using The Widget"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:48
#: b0d943b26b9c4cc9bbbfc258b49db7a7
msgid ""
"To detach a device, click the Qubes Devices Widget icon again. Attached "
"devices are displayed in bold. Hover the one you want to detach. A list of "
"VMs appears, one showing the eject symbol: |eject icon|"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:169
#: fcda37121fe8491bb938cc4fdab4e173
msgid "eject icon"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:51
#: 202b17e5afef443c9e8f3589845471f3
msgid "Attaching a Device to Several VMs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:54
#: 5b9f8dc17fc549fbab66e74103f0df56
msgid ""
"Only ``mic`` should be attached to more than one running VM. You may "
"*assign* a device to more than one VM (using the ``--persistent`` option), "
"however, only one of them can be started at the same time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:56
#: e7691e8d5b1e491ca2b6f65320410fb7
msgid ""
"But be careful: There is a `bug in <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-"
"issues/issues/4692>`__ ``qvm-device block`` or ``qvm-block`` which will "
"allow you to *attach* a block device to two running VMs. Don’t do that!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:59
#: 29809c063e0a4c4aa55d30266361d8e4
msgid "General ``qvm-device`` Command Line Tool Behavior"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:62
#: 8c97771662c24885bd521b8878e11012
msgid ""
"All devices, including PCI-devices, may be attached from the commandline "
"using the ``qvm-device``-tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:65
#: 206d61a71f6e491db37f3acd8fbc553b
msgid "Device Classes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:68
#: c757741272ab4469b7a1e97adfb6c727
msgid ""
"``qvm-device`` expects DEVICE_CLASS as first argument. DEVICE_CLASS can be "
"one of"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:70
#: cba6d3fa8f4141978c2f7ddb4236eae6
msgid "``pci``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:72
#: 9b5b1048399a4c0b92e3715e4ab76534
msgid "``usb``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:74
#: e887b2e1254449b89e9677ab5b731abf
msgid "``block``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:76
#: bd4d1504589d48c1a41d96de11a04fb2
msgid "``mic``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:81
#: 2717786a89f644a4b65c092db665cdf2
msgid "``qvm-device`` Actions"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:84
#: b5d62c7096d3470ab00cad9bec0461c0
msgid "``qvm-device`` supports three actions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:86
#: c5e20680374d4073ba7f2fc505106a8e
msgid "``list`` (ls, l) - list all devices of DEVICE_CLASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:88
#: c8cc9144001f41f48f7b566e8aff7f8e
msgid "``attach`` (at, a) - attach a specific device of DEVICE_CLASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:90
#: b65ee60f481a4511bdd47844eb4cbfca
msgid "``detach`` (dt, d) - detach a specific device of DEVICE_CLASS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:95
#: 943ef3733f404925aa5c3b1734d4ddb3
msgid "Global Options"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:98
#: 0ffc26c4ff2a4972bf7156d412fcf7ca
msgid "These three options are always available:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:100
#: 7a3f4aee8adc45de8abf7fd3c091e35e
msgid "``--help``, ``-h`` - show help message and exit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:102
#: 6917306203c84d29bc33c4b9766da83e
msgid "``--verbose``, ``-v`` - increase verbosity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:104
#: 0f52b154d977441fb5412bbc07961f8e
msgid "``--quiet``, ``-q`` - decrease verbosity"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:108
#: 4c108385d8194f34b67154a952ba4cca
msgid ""
"A full command consists of one DEVICE_CLASS and one action. If no action is "
"given, list is implied. DEVICE_CLASS however is required."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:110
#: 7126054654b544c7890df4a6e07e1da3
msgid ""
"**SYNOPSIS**: ``qvm-device DEVICE_CLASS {action} [action-specific arguments]"
" [options]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:116
#: 8e53f7596d064028bdd2e13b93aed6b2
msgid "Actions"
msgstr "Actions"

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:121
#: d076bc3e5c2f452e959d2dd643720d60
msgid ""
"Actions are applicable to every DEVICE_CLASS and expose some additional "
"options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:124
#: 3719ddde971b45039e74841fe343d5c2
msgid "Listing Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:127
#: fed27364044f47c1b93a678fef227ca4
msgid ""
"The ``list`` action lists known devices in the system. ``list`` accepts VM-"
"names to narrow down listed devices. Devices available in, as well as "
"attached to the named VMs will be listed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:129
#: fc8d2b06d5664215982290edc224e44b
msgid "``list`` accepts two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:131
#: 5c88dcc97ed74d26a97d9b181150190f
msgid ""
"``--all`` - equivalent to specifying every VM name after ``list``. No VM-"
"name implies ``--all``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:133
#: 9f5a20dc9b1c4774be013615ad09d95a
msgid "``--exclude`` - exclude VMs from ``--all``. Requires ``--all``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:137
#: 81028a5fcdad411ab0e0ee47bbe36335
msgid ""
"**SYNOPSIS** ``qvm-device DEVICE_CLASS {list|ls|l} [--all [--exclude VM [VM "
"[...]]] | VM [VM [...]]]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:140
#: 84f8a7a4ae6a41bea4e071b1052837bf
msgid "Attaching Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:143
#: 9c25a7a63ea1448a9880de00e025e9e5
msgid ""
"The ``attach`` action assigns an exposed device to a VM. This makes the "
"device available in the VM it’s attached to. Required argument are targetVM "
"and sourceVM:deviceID. (sourceVM:deviceID can be determined from ``list`` "
"output)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:145
#: 33e5f6116aab4d639d82d54206f2a090
msgid "``attach`` accepts two options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:147
#: 77f79a72bed1419c8b0ec615079db01c
msgid ""
"``--persistent`` - attach device on targetVM-boot. If the device is "
"unavailable (physically missing or sourceVM not started), booting the "
"targetVM fails."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:149
#: 049dbba1292a4b7d96394c4a8e6a51b6
msgid ""
"``--option``, ``-o`` - set additional options specific to DEVICE_CLASS."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:153
#: 56efc885f1784428970a3499c693da08
msgid ""
"**SYNOPSIS** ``qvm-device DEVICE_CLASS {attach|at|a} targetVM "
"sourceVM:deviceID [options]``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:156
#: 1b3dadb2bdb540c2a415a9e519977747
msgid "Detaching Devices"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:159
#: 790c346758a84974af56f2f637e7462f
msgid ""
"The ``detach`` action removes an assigned device from a targetVM. It won’t "
"be available afterwards anymore. Though it tries to do so gracefully, beware"
" that data-connections might be broken unexpectedly, so close any "
"transaction before detaching a device!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:161
#: 218b65267909483c870865d6215ad2e5
msgid ""
"If no specific ``sourceVM:deviceID`` combination is given, *all devices of "
"that DEVICE_CLASS will be detached.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:163
#: 3d88b6fa64084bcdb7f2cddfbf97f79a
msgid "``detach`` accepts no options."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/how-to-guides/how-to-use-devices.rst:165
#: 59672076713e4fa88812b1ae1838d775
msgid ""
"**SYNOPSIS** ``qvm-device DEVICE_CLASS {detach|dt|d} targetVM "
"[sourceVM:deviceID]``"
msgstr ""
